Wawrinka Beats Australia’s Hewitt, Gives Switzerland Davis Cup Playoff Win

-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 
2011-09-19T01:42:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/wawrinka-beats-australia-s-hewitt-gives-switzerland-davis-cup-playoff-win.html
Stanislas Wawrinka beatLleyton Hewitt in a match carried over from yesterday to give
 Switzerland  a 3-2 victory against Australia in their Davis Cup
tennis playoff.  Wawrinka, the world No. 19, wrapped up a 4-6, 6-4, 6-7 (7-
9), 6-4, 6-3 win as Hewitt was unable to hold his serve on
resumption of the match on grass at Royal Sydney Golf Club.
Wawrinka had led 5-3 in the deciding set when fading light
halted play yesterday.  The victory earned Switzerland promotion into the elite
World Group of the premier team competition in men’s tennis.
Third-ranked Roger Federer yesterday sent the best-of-five
contest into a decider with a four-set win over  Bernard Tomic .  Spain and Argentina will meet in this year’s final after
winning their semifinals yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  